Analysis of the water samples has been completed.
XXX collected in the area were studied as the primary specimen in this analysis, which came to conclusions as follows:
① The pH value and chloride content of the water at the area is within the normal range;
② The water source has a relatively high insoluble content. A potential problem of water pollution is suspected;
③ Active presence of MO around has resulted in high levels of Wutherium Compounds;
④ ......
Summarizing the points above, we could come to an opinion that the area is not suitble for a new site as indexes exceed standards of habitable environments.

The spectroscopic analysis of the soil samples has been completed.
Flower Shrooms growing at this area were studied as the primiary sample in this analysis, which has come to conclusions as follows:
① The soil has a high content of moisture and organic matter in the environment at this site;
② The soil is mixed with certain impurities and has caused soil contamination;
③ ......
Summarizing the points above, we could come to an opinion that the area is not suitble for a new site as indexes exceed standards of habitable environments.

Analysis of the biospecimen has been completed.
Bird Eggs collected in the area were studied as the primary specimen in this analysis, which came to conclusions as follows:
① Organisms living in the area tend to be more dynamic, possibly showing certain degrees of aggression to human;
② Wutherium Compound presence in the organisms living in this area far exceeds average level. It is suspected that Tacet Fields might be active in near-by areas;
③......
Summarizing the points above, we could come to an opinion that the area is not suitble for a new site as indexes exceed standards of habitable environments.
